---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionMenu from '../components/SectionMenu.astro';
import headshot from '../assets/photos/headshot.jpeg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Derek Dombek"
  description="From touring musician to U.S. Army veteran to software developer — the story of how Derek Dombek found his way into tech."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1><Image class="headshot" src={headshot} alt="Portrait of Derek Dombek" width={150} height={150} /></h1>
    <hr class="rule" />
  </section>

  <section class="paper prose">
    <p>
      Hi! I'm Derek. I was born in Florida, raised in Cleveland, and reside in lovely Boise, Idaho. I skipped the traditional college route early on because I was too busy living out of a van, playing music, and touring the country. 
    </p>
    <p>
      Eventually, the road caught up with me, so in 2013 I decided to mix things up in a big way and joined the U.S. Army. It was a crash course in growing up. A deployment to Afghanistan introduced me to an incredible mix of people from all walks of life and taught me how to stay cool, calm, and collected when things get chaotic.
    </p>
    <p>
      While deployed, I spent a lot of time reflecting on what I wanted to do after. I’ve always enjoying creating and learning how random things work holistically, and that’s when the computer science lightbulb finally went off. After getting back, I dove headfirst into software engineering. I quickly realized coding is exactly like being a mechanic—except the grease is just a massive coffee habit. 
    </p>
    <p>
      The tech world moves fast, but I'm excited to be here to build cool stuff and relationships, so please reach out!
    </p>
  </section>

  <SectionMenu />
</BaseLayout>
